main event: A witness observed an unidentified flying object near Cleveland, Ohio on November 9, 1965.
interesting points: The object was described as bright, glowing, and oblong in shape.
The object appeared to be traveling at a high rate of speed and made a humming sound.
The object hovered in the sky and then rapidly accelerated and disappeared.
The witness provided a sketch of the object, which showed a hexagonal or hexagon-shaped exhaust or vapor trail.
The Air Force's Project Blue Book investigated the sighting but stated that the information provided was not sufficient for evaluation.
